WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified body profile for the ARRI ALEXA 35 camera. It contains the
exact mathematical IDT (Input Device Transform), LogC4 curve parameters
with their inverse, native color space primaries, white balance presets,
ISO sensitivity ranges, and dual gain mode specifications. This is the
single source of truth for linearizing ALEXA 35 footage to scene-referred
ACES2065-1.

WHY IT EXISTS
ARRI’s REVEAL Color Science uses the AWG4 (ARRI Wide Gamut 4) color space
and LogC4 encoding. To integrate ALEXA 35 footage into an ACES or GIOP
pipeline, every pixel must be exactly linearized. Without this certified
body file, downstream compositing, grading, and VFX will inherit
approximation errors. This file provides the mathematically auditable
IDT, eliminating the black-box LUT.

HOW IT WORKS
The file defines the transform chain:
  1. Inverse LogC4 (using the EI-dependent formula) → linear AWG4 RGB.
  2. AWG4 to ACES2065-1 matrix (3x3 certified).
  3. White balance scaling (as-shot or preset).
  4. Dual gain sensor mode metadata and ISO calibration.
All constants are provided for all supported Exposure Indices (EI 160–6400).

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
